# Apache Ignite PoC Implementation

## Introduction

The Apache Poc Consists of the TMS service, a subset of rules and a database config file found [here](https://github.com/tazama-lf/ignite-poc)

## Getting Started

We will be deploying Apache ignite via Docker, but you are free to install natively as well if you wish. 

## Setting Up Apache Ignite

### Using Docker Desktop

1. Starting of, open your docker desktop. Navigate to images on the left-hand side, and click on the search bar at the top.

![Docker Desktop Search](Images/ApacheIgniteInstall_1.png)

2. Search for: "ApacheIgnite" and select the latest apacheignite/ignite image. Click on the pull command. 

![alt text](Images/ApacheIgniteInstall_2.png)

3. Once it is done, you want to navigate back to images to ensure your image was pulled correctly. Once you see it, you want to click on the little play button inline with the image.

![alt text](Images/ApacheIgniteInstall_3.png)

4. When running the image, you will be greeting with a config screen, expand the "Optional Settings". You will now see a range of ports, a volume bind and environmental variables.

It is recommended to expose all the ports. For the volume host you want to navigate to a location on your server for the persistent data, and link it to the: "/storage" location, since this is the location our ignite will use.

Next you want to configure the "CONFIG_URI" environmental variable and pass it the path from the Ignite home directory to the working directory. The easiest way to do this is to also put your config file in the storage location.

![alt text](Images/ApacheIgniteInstall_4.png)

5. Once you're done and you ran the image, you will be able to navigate to the containers tab and see your database running - 

![alt text](Images/ApacheIgniteInstall_5.png)


