For our database management software we used [dbeaver](https://dbeaver.io/download/). You can use whichever database management software works for you. 

### Ensuring your db was deployed correctly

We will use dbeaver for these instructions. 

1. Open the database connection model - if this is your first database on the system, it will open automaticaly.

![alt text](Images/dbeaver_1.png)

2. Search for Apache, you should see the filter show you Apache ignite. Select it. 

![alt text](Images/dbeaver_2.png)

3. Switch to URL and enter your URL (By default this will be localhost:10800 if you're hosting this on your local machine). This should start with the pre-pend value they add automatically.

![alt text](Images/dbeaver_3.png)

4. If this is the first time using Apache Ignite connection, you will have to install the drivers for it. Dbeaver will automaticaly find them and prompt you to install them. 

