## Setting Cluster to Active

To set the Apache-Ignite cluster to Active, which will allow you to execute SQL queries as well as perform operations as the tms, you will need to execute the following commands in the Apache Ignite Pod. 

``
cd apache-ignite/bin
./control.sh --set-state ACTIVE
``

Follow the on screen prompt to enable the cluster. 

## Running TMS

Next step is to run the TMS service found [here](https://github.com/tazama-lf/ignite-poc/tree/dev/TMS)

You can use a local run if you want to debug, by cloning the solution and running the following npm commands: 

``
npm run build
npm run start
``

You can also run the docker file if you want a containerized version. 

Most of the normal env variables are still required, baring any arango ones, but a new one is now present: 

``
DATABASE_URL='127.0.0.1:10800'
``

This is your Ignite db url. Please note - During the time of the PoC there is no security enabled.

